body:
I would create a new environment. 
These are recently updated, please use this: http://www.mousemotorlab.org/s/dlc-windowsGPU-x2rt.yaml

Hi Mackenzie,

unfortunately I got this error now after downloading the correct .yaml file 

![DLC_error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36044114/66718847-b9fbe700-ede8-11e9-9fcc-7bbe43c4161f.jpg)

I am most likely overlooking something super easy.
You need to be in the folder where you downloaded the file, i.e. `C:\Users\imgross\Downloads\` or wherever you move the file to, then you can call "create env..."
Yes, I went the folder where the correct .yaml file is. In my case (C:\Users\imgross\.conda\envs\)
Is there a name inside the yaml? I guess that’s the direct error message

It says this when I open the .yaml file, so I guess a name is indicated, right?

![DLC_yaml](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36044114/66759665-f4c15600-eea0-11e9-8631-23ce81ed15b4.png)
Okay thanks for checking, in the above terminal image it seems you are calling the “CPU” version though

Yes, that was the mistake. Sorry, my bad!

But thanks for your patience :)
No problem! (I’ll close, but let me know if installation is working)

Hi Mackenzie,

I did the installation and it looked as if it worked. But when I import deeplabcut this message pops up:

![DLC_after_update](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36044114/67403097-c551ce00-f5b1-11e9-9aac-3259bd2e2f35.png)

and if I try to analyze videos with the pretrained network from the older version I get the following warning:

![DLC_after_update2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36044114/67403159-d8649e00-f5b1-11e9-9cdf-6874ce7bafdd.png)


Do I need to change something about my Tensorflow?

Cheers,
Isa
No they are just warnings that numpy and tensorflow are changing, we will be updating code in future releases to be prepared

Okay.

And below the second warning I get this error:

![DLC_after_update3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36044114/67407731-3dbb8d80-f5b8-11e9-8d7c-b591787851cb.png)
Could you help me out with that error?

You need to ensure that your driver version matches or exceeds your CUDA Toolkit version.

See https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut/blob/master/docs/installation.md#troubleshooting
And
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3253257/cuda-driver-version-is-insufficient-for-cuda-runtime-version
